# app4.js - Error Handeling
- using trycatch
- using error route handler
- err - err is the error object passed to Express error-handling middleware when something goes wrong during request processing.
- Normal middleware: (req, res, next)
  Error middleware: (err, req, res, next)
- The first parameter (err) tells Express this is an error handler

Request → Middleware → Route Handler
               ↓
           next(err)
               ↓
        Error Handler (err, req, res, next)

note - error handeling middleware - should be written in the end of routes

